name: white chicken chili

food.name: pepper or hot sauce, ready to serve

instructions:
1. In a medium pot, heat 1 teaspoon of oil over moderate heat. 

2. Add onion rings, cook (turning occasionally) until soft and golden. Remove onions and set aside, leaving any remaining oil in pot. 

3. Creating the roux: Add remaining oil over low heat, and whisk in flour. Cook the roux mixture, whisking constantly until light brown/golden color.

4. Stir in the onions and gradually add the beer, half-and-half and 1/4 cup of the broth. Allow the liquids to absorb into roux before adding rest of broth. 

5. Continue to whisk constantly. Bring mixture to a gentle boil, then reduce to a simmer, stirring occasionally (about 5 minutes or until thickened). 

6. Stir in chili powder, salt, black pepper and hot sauce.

7. Add beans, peppers, and chicken and cook mixture over moderately low heat, stirring occasionally for approx. 20 minutes. 

8. Dice avocado and garnish chili with avocado before serving.
